	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: What's the purpose of 1k resistor between battery and SR</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />IIRC, the resistor was in series with the battery. I assume it's there to reduce transient current consumption on switchover, since 1k is much too small to help prevent charging the battery through the diodes.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


